First, unrelated to your error message but a serious matter: Your 
&#39;operatorContactUrl&#39; value needs to be a web URL that includes 
information about your crawl and how to contact you if there are any 
problems.

Your current value, &lt;http://www.archieve.org&gt;, is troubling under any 
interpretation. (If it&#39;s your real domain, it has no crawl-operator 
contact info in the event of crawl problems; if you&#39;ve tried to enter 
*our* domain, then it means we could get misdirected complaints about 
your crawling that we would be powerless to address.)

Regarding the error you&#39;re seeingg:

I don&#39;t see any changes in your file, compared to the bundled 
configuration that is known to work, that might cause the &#39;BdbModule not 
started&#39; error.

Are you sure this is the CXML that&#39;s being built?

Can you start fresh from the standard configuration and see if the same 
error recurs?

If it does, can you include more of the error stack/error message for 
context?

- Gordon @ IA


